### Conclusion

The scientific literature unequivocally supports the transformative potential of graphene in enhancing adhesive performance. From significantly boosting mechanical strengths and toughness to imparting electrical conductivity and improving thermal management, graphene-modified glues are poised to meet the escalating demands of modern engineering. As research continues to refine dispersion techniques and reduce material costs, graphene-enhanced adhesives will undoubtedly become a cornerstone in advanced manufacturing, enabling stronger, smarter, and more durable bonding solutions across a multitude of industries.
